\
"I am clear not only that it is possible to include financial services within a trade deal but that it is very much in our mutual interest to do so," Mr. Hammond is planning to say. He is due to stress that "every trade deal is unique" and financial services shouldn't automatically be ruled out.\
\
British officials have acknowledged that after Britain leaves the EU in March next year, the U.K. will have to give up its financial district's cherished "passport" that allows financial institutions based in London to trade freely across the EU's other 27 member states. Firms that lack such as passport must set up subsidiaries within the EU, raising the prospect that banks and insurers could decamp from London.\
\
